dpypr.main.fetch_all_global_df(globals_dict)[source]

Returns all objects beginning with ‘df_’ in global space as a list.

dpypr.main.fetch_all_sqlite_tables(path)[source]

Returns all table names present in a sqlite database as a list. r

dpypr.main.gather_data_dictionary(globals_dict)[source]

Packages all objects in input dictionary beginning with ‘df_’ and returns output dictionary.

dpypr.main.headers_to_snakecase(df, uppercase=False)[source]

Converts all column headers to lower snake case by defatul and uppercase if ‘uppercase’ argument is True.

dpypr.main.optimise_numeric_datatypes(df)[source]

Optimises the data types in a pandas DataFrame by attempting to convert strings to numerical data where possible and to the smallest possible integer datatype.

dpypr.main.read_all_csv(path)[source]

Iteratively loads data.csv from the data directory and assign to dataframes. Unpacks dictionary to global variables names with the format df_{filename}.

Iteratively loads data.feather from the data directory and assign to dataframes. Unpacks dictionary to global variables names with the format df_{filename}.

dpypr.main.read_all_pickle(path)[source]

Iteratively loads data.pickle from the data directory and assign to dataframes. Unpacks dictionary to global variables names with the format df_{filename}.

dpypr.main.read_all_sqlite(path)[source]

Returns all data from a sqlite database as a dictionary.

dpypr.main.read_all_xlsx(path)[source]

Iteratively loads data.xlsx from the data directory and assign to dataframes. Unpacks dictionary to global variables names with the format df_{filename}.

Outputs info logging mesage to console with variable sleep timer.

  • Prefix allows user to rename processed files upon writing.

  • ‘Messaging’ allows user to output number of records to console.
